<h1 class="sepBar"><span id="dnn_ctr514724_dnnDealerTitle_titleLabel" class="Head">Welcome to Universal Auto Sales and Classic Cars</span>


</h1>
<div id="dnn_ctr514724_ContentPane"><!-- Start_Module_514724 --><div id="dnn_ctr514724_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent ModDCSModulesWelcomeTextC">
	
    
    
<div class="DCSWelcomeText_Main"> 
    <span id="dnn_ctr514724_WelcomeText_lblWelcomeText" class="WelcomeText_Label"><p>Welcome to Universal Auto Sales and Classic Cars. We are located in Linthicum, MD minutes from downtown Baltimore, as well as Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport.</p>

<p>We would like to take this time to tell you a little bit about us and who you will be dealing with when it comes to the purchase of one of our cars! We are a small family-owned and operated business that has a true love and appreciation for all classics and muscle cars. First and foremost we are “car guys” and huge enthusiasts of this hobby/sport and always have been for as long as we can remember. Our passion spills over to the quality of cars we sell. We do not consign cars, every car you see here on our website we own. This allows us to take the time to go over each car to make sure it is as safe and sound as possible and to make sure it is what’s advertised.</p>

<p>We not only sell classic and muscle cars but we restore, build and repair all makes of classics and muscle cars too! We have a shop right here at our showroom and if we can’t fix it, restore it or build it, we know who can.</p>

<p>Bottom line is you are not just purchasing another used car from a bunch of used car salesmen. We do not have “balloons” and “gorillas” out in front of our showroom. You are buying a quality car at a reasonable price from a bunch of “GEARHEADS” just like you!!</p>

<p>Please call us at 888-519-0812 or visit our website at <a style="color:#0000ff;text-decoration:underline;" href="http://www.universalautosalesandclassiccars.com">www.universalautosalesandclassiccars.com</a> to view our complete inventory.</p>

<p>Thanks for taking the time to check our cars and look forward to hearing from you.</p></span>
</div>

</div><!-- End_Module_514724 --></div></div><div class="DnnModule DnnModule-DNN_HTML DnnModule-514725"><a name="514725"></a>

<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10px;">Universal Auto Sales and Classic Cars, Inc. strives to be as accurate and honest as possible in disclosing as much correct information about any of our listed vehicles. Our information not only comes from the previous owner but from our own professional observations. We want you to be happy with your decision in purchasing a vehicle from us and to feel comfortable that your decision was the right one for you. You must recognize that we are dealing with vehicles that are 30+ years old; that they probably had more than one owner; and that they were restored to that previous owner&rsquo;s specs and not yours. Therefore, Universal Auto Sales and Classic Cars, Inc. will not be held responsible for any false facts that we were provided and that is listed about any vehicle. We do not guarantee and will not warranty any vehicle, its equipment or options. All problems or concerns must be addressed prior to the completion of sale. All sales are final. To protect yourself you should come to our showroom and check the car out thoroughly for yourself. If that is not possible you should hire an outside inspection/appraisal company to check it out for you. We have a three bay repair/restoration shop on the premises equipped with lifts and tools that are available to you if needed. We can help in the arrangements with travel and inspections as well. The owners/employees at Universal are first and foremost enthusiasts about this hobby/sport. We understand your concerns and want to be as honest and helpful as possible in your decision in buying one of our vehicles. Thank you.<br />
